Its key offerings include Zillow, Trulia, StreetEasy, and HotPads, among others, which collectively cater to various stakeholders such as renters, buyers, sellers, and real estate professionals through comprehensive property listings and innovative tools like the Zestimate valuation feature. Additionally, Zillow has ventured into direct home-buying and selling services with Zillow Offers, aligning its business model with evolving consumer preferences and the digitization of real estate transactions.

security.name: Consolidated Communications Holdings, Inc.
security.description: Consolidated Communications Holdings, Inc., based in the United States, operates primarily in the telecommunications industry, delivering a wide range of services including high-speed internet, phone, and digital TV to customers across a multi-state area. The company is particularly focused on enhancing broadband service capabilities and expanding fiber networks. A key project that underscores its strategic emphasis is the upgrading and expansion of its fiber-optic network to support enhanced speed and service reliability for residential and business customers, aiming to reach at least 70% of its serviceable areas with high-speed fiber internet. This project aligns with its objective to become a leading broadband provider and upgrade its infrastructure to support future communication needs. Consolidated Communications is also heavily invested in improving network efficiency and customer service technologies to support its long-term growth and sustainability goals.

security.name: ArcelorMittal S.A. - Depositary Receipt (Common Stock)
security.description: ArcelorMittal S.A. is a globally prominent steel and mining company with its headquarters in Luxembourg. As one of the world's leading steel manufacturers, the company plays a pivotal role in the metallurgical sector, providing a wide array of steel products used in various industries including automotive, construction, household appliances, and packaging. ArcelorMittal is also actively involved in significant mining operations, making it one of the largest iron ore producers globally. Its key projects often focus on sustainable practices and technological innovations aimed at reducing environmental impact and improving efficiency in steel production. Through strategic investments and collaborations, ArcelorMittal continues to expand its footprint and enhance its operational capabilities worldwide.

security.name: Dollar General Corporation
security.description: Dollar General Corporation, headquartered in the United States, operates as a prominent player in the discount retail sector. Primarily, the company focuses on offering a wide range of products including consumables, seasonal items, home products, and apparel, all at low everyday prices. Dollar General has established a significant footprint with its extensive network of over 18,000 stores across 47 states, making it one of the most widespread retail chains in the U.S. A key part of its strategy includes the DG Fresh initiative aimed at enhancing its fresh and frozen product offerings. Moreover, the company is advancing in digital transformation while consistently working on store expansion and remodeling projects to further drive customer engagement and operational efficiency.

security.name: Alliant Energy Corporation
security.description: Alliant Energy Corporation, based in the United States, primarily operates in the utility sector, focusing on the production and distribution of electricity and natural gas. Headquartered in Madison, Wisconsin, the company primarily serves customers in Iowa and Wisconsin. One key initiative by Alliant Energy is its commitment to sustainable energy solutions, as evidenced by its ongoing investments in renewable energy projects, including wind and solar power developments. These projects align with its goal to reduce carbon emissions and enhance energy efficiency across its operations. Alliant’s strategic focus extends to modernizing infrastructure and promoting energy conservation programs to ensure reliable service while supporting environmental stewardship.

security.name: Freeport-McMoRan Inc.
security.description: Freeport-McMoRan Inc., based in the United States, is a leading international mining corporation primarily involved in the exploration and production of copper, gold, and molybdenum. The company's major operations are strategically located in North America, South America, and Indonesia. Among its key projects, the Grasberg mining complex in Indonesia stands out as one of the largest copper and gold mines globally. Additionally, the company manages significant mining operations in the Americas, including notable sites like Morenci and Bagdad in Arizona, which contribute substantially to its copper production capabilities. Freeport-McMoRan’s active global presence and extensive project portfolio underline its influential position within the primary minerals and metals industry.
